<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.60.9-10_0001a" />

<note type="curatorial">280-2 Aly Collection </note>

<opener>
<dateline>Dec. 26, 69</dateline>

<salute><hi rend="double underline">Dear</hi> Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Yesterday Florence read the final chapter to me and recorded on a separate sheet the few corrections and suggestions I made. She will type the sheet and send it to you.</p>
</div1>

<div1 type="letter">
<opener><salute><hi rend="underline">Dear Lady:</hi></salute></opener>
<p>It's a lovely job, and I'm happy about it. We intended to drive to Skyrim tomorrow,

<pb facs="nei.j4c.60.9-10_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>

but it's snowing busily, and we may have to postpone our trip a day or two. But <hi rend="underline">when</hi> we go, we'll take the chapter for my girls to read.</p>

<p>I <hi rend="underline">do</hi> hope you can know more about a publisher <hi rend="underline">reasonably</hi> <hi rend="double underline">soon.</hi> I <hi rend="underline">need very much to know</hi> what you do with the biography before I can go ahead with a <hi rend="double underline">new contract</hi> with the U. of Neb. Press.</p>

<p> <hi rend="double underline">I</hi> wish you <hi rend="underline">could</hi>  

<note type="authorial">I'm sending two <hi rend="double underline">strong</hi> letters.</note>

<fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.60.9-10_0002"/>
<fw type="authorial"><unclear>-</unclear>3-</fw>

get Random or some other big publisher. I fear, however, that this may not be possible, considering the "Mod" mood that is abroad. Still, who knows? There is a tremendous backlog of material to follow your book, if someone has the vision and daring necessary.</p>

<p> <hi rend="underline">Is</hi> there <hi rend="underline">any</hi> reason why where should be much more delay in</p>



<note type="authorial">Hello, Bower!!</note>

<gap reason="missing" extent="1 page" />

